From crawling under homes in search of the deadly brown snake to saving pets from giant pythons – it’s just another typical day for Richie Gilbert.

It all started at the age of five when he showed his mum his catch of the day. Not only was it the first snake he had ever caught, it was one of the world’s most venomous - the copperhead.

But that close encounter with disaster didn't deter the boy from the Sunshine Coast from turning his backyard hobby  into a career as a qualified snake catcher.

