‘A lot of people think it’s a dangerous job but to me, I feel like it’s not dangerous at all,’ Mr Gilbert told Daily Mail Australia.

'There are people risking their lives everyday - like electricians or people parachuting and jumping out of planes - to me that's dangerous but its all relative to risk management.

‘But I've been doing it for a long time and I can't put my finger on what attracted me to them but I have always loved chasing snakes since I was little.

'And I love snakes for different reasons - like the venomous ones give me an adrenaline kick when I catch them.'

